<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 12:29AM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Randolph, northeastern Fulton and northeastern Sharp Counties through
100 AM CDT...
At 1229 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hardy, or 9 miles southeast of Mammoth Spring, moving southeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Highland in Sharp County...       Hardy...
Armstrong...                      Ozark Acres...
Saddler Falls...                  Eleven Point...
Wirth...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
